==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repulsive
<hw>Re*pul"sive</hw> <pr>(-s?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pulsif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving, or able, to
repulse; repellent; <as>as, a <ex>repulsive</ex> force</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Repulsive</qex> of his might the weapon stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cold; forbidding; offensive; <as>as,
<ex>repulsive</ex> manners</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*pul"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*pul"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repulsory</ent>⟦br⟧
